    "uses": "Amlodipine is primarily used to manage hypertension, which helps to prevent complications such as heart attack, stroke, and kidney problems. It is also used in the treatment of angina, particularly in patients who experience chest pain due to coronary artery disease. Additionally, it may be beneficial for patients with certain types of heart failure, as it helps to improve heart muscle function and reduce symptoms related to fluid retention.\n\nIn some cases, amlodipine may be prescribed off-label for conditions such as Raynaud's phenomenon, a condition that affects blood flow to the extremities, causing pain and discomfort. It may also be used in combination with other antihypertensive agents to enhance blood pressure control and provide a synergistic effect for better management of cardiovascular diseases.",
